ent of Greece]] in the [[Hellenic Parliament]] and became the first woman to hold the office, succeeding [[Prokopis Pavlopoulos]]. Sakellaropoulou suspended the protocol ceremony for the inauguration scheduled for Saturday 14 and no handshakes were allowed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/greeces-female-president-sworn-69576512|title=Greece's first female president is sworn in|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2020-03-13/greece-swears-in-first-female-president-no-handshakes-amid-coronavirus|title=Greece Swears in First Female President, No Handshakes Amid Coronavirus|website=US News|language=en|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n* On 14 March, 38 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 228, while six more were released from hospitals, bringing the recovered total to eight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/211239/koronoios-38-nea-kroysmata-ta-perissotera-stin-athina|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 38 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 - \u03a4\u03b1 \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03c3\u03cc\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=14 March 2020|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> A 90-year-old man hospitalised in [[Ptolemaida]] died.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/211188/koronoios-kai-deyteros-nekros-apo-ton-io|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b4\u03b5\u03cd\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03cc\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03b9\u03cc|last=Newsroom|date=14 March 2020|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> Also, a 67-year-old man hospitalised in Zakynthos died, bringing the country death toll to three.<ref>{{Cite 