anguage=el-GR|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n*On 24 March, 48 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 743, while three people were released from hospitals, bringing the recovered total to 32. Three more people died due to the virus, bringing the country death toll to 20.<ref name=\"cnn.gr\">{{cite Web |title= \u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 20 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 - 743 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/212585/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|website=cnn.gr|date=24 March 2020|language=el}}</ref> A 40-year-old woman, who had died three days previously, was found to have been positive for the virus making her, by far, the youngest victim of the pandemic in Greece.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.newsit.gr/topikes-eidhseis/koronoios-thetiki-40xroni-pou-exase-ti-zoi-tis-sta-koresteia-kastorias/3000091/ |title = \u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0398\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae 40\u03c7\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b7 \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03ad\u03c7\u03b1\u03c3\u03b5 \u03c4\u03b7 \u03b6\u03c9\u03ae \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u039a\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac - \u0395\u03b9\u03b4\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2|date = 24 March 2020}}</ref> The new President of Greece, [[Katerina Sakellaropoulou]], declared she was going to address the nation on the evening of the 24th regarding both the COVID-19 pandemic and the [[Celebration of the Greek Revolution|25th of March]] Independence Day celebrations.\n*On 25 March, 78 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 821, while four people were released from hospitals, bringing the recovered total to 36. Two more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 22.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tovima.gr/2020/03/25/society/stous-22-oi-nekroi-apo-koronoio-stin-ellada-821-ta-krousmata-synolika/|title= \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 22 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u2013 78 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1, 821 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac|date=2020-03-25|website=tovima.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n*On 26 March, 71 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 892, while six people were released from hospitals, bringing the recovered total to 42. Four more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 26.<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/212862/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 26 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 71 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 |last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-26|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n*On 27 March, 74 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 966, while ten people were released from hospitals, bringing the recovered total to 52. Two more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 28.<ref name=\"ReferenceC\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213013/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 28 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 74 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-27|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n*On 28 March, 95 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1061. Four more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 32.<ref name=\"ReferenceD\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213127/live-h-enimerosi-tsiodra-xardalia-gia-ton-koronoio|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9\u03cc\u03c2: 32 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9, 95 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1, 1.061 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-28|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*On 29 March, 95 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the county total to 1156, while one person was released from Alexandroupoli University hospital, bringing the recovered total to 53. Six more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 38.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213204/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 38 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 - 95 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 |last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-29|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n*On 30 March, 56 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the county total to 1212. Five more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 43.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213373/koronoios-43-thanatoi-56-nea-kroysmata-sta-1-212-synolika|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 43 \u03b8\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03b9, 56 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1, \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1 1.212 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac |last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-30|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n*On 31 March, 102 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1314. Six more deaths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 49.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213525/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 49 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 82 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-31|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> Twenty of the cases are aboard a passenger ship stationed out of the port of Piraeus. It carried 382 persons, including 36 Greeks, 150 Turks, 83 Indonesians and others. At least some of the persons were Turkish workers travelling to Spain but the ship was turned back to Turkey when the cases were identified. It was not accepted in Turkey and since 21st of March is at Piraeus.<ref>[https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-karantina-peiraia-kroyazieroploio \"Coronavirus: In quarantine at Piraeus the cruiser 'El. Venizelos' with the 20 cases\", iefimerida, 31-3-2020]</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===COVID-19 Cases in Greece===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Date\n!Confirmed\nNew \n!Deaths\nNew\n!Confirmed\n\nTotal \n!Deaths\nTotal\n!Recoveries\n!Hospitalised\n!Intensive Care\n!Accumulative total<br>tests performed\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 26 February\n|1\n| 0\n|1\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 27 February<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eody.gov.gr/enimerosi-diapisteymenon-syntakton-ygeias-gia-tis-exelixeis-anaforika-me-to-neo-koronoio/|t